OL,3,CWarning over 'worryingly hot'
OL,4,Cclassrooms as climate change worsens
OL,5,Cheatwaves
OL,7,FCampaigners are warning of "worryingly
OL,8,Fhot" temperatures affecting children
OL,9,Fand teachers in classrooms as climate
OL,10,Fchange drives more heatwaves.
OL,12,FThe warning comes after research
OL,13,Fshowed classrooms breached a
OL,14,Frecommended maximum temperature of 26C
OL,15,Fduring the recent heatwave in late
OL,16,FJune.
