OL,3,CWarning over 'worryingly hot'
OL,4,Cclassrooms as climate change worsens
OL,5,Cheatwaves
OL,7,FA study by climate campaign group
OL,8,FRound Our Way worked with teachers in
OL,9,Fseven schools across England to put
OL,10,Fsensors in classrooms that recorded
OL,11,Fthe temperature automatically every
OL,12,Fhour over a period of four weeks.
OL,14,FThe period included the late June
OL,15,Fheatwave, when the UK's Health
OL,16,FSecurity Agency (UKHSA) issued a
OL,17,Fyellow heat health alert for most of
OL,18,FEngland as temperatures climbed to 30C.
