OL,3,CWarning over 'worryingly hot'
OL,4,Cclassrooms as climate change worsens
OL,5,Cheatwaves
OL,7,FThe data found that, while there is no
OL,8,Flegal maximum temperature for schools
OL,9,For workplaces, temperatures in six of
OL,10,Fthe seven schools exceeded the 26C
OL,11,Fmaximum which is advised by the
OL,12,FNational Education Union (NEU).
OL,14,FThe highest peak indoor temperature
OL,15,Frecorded was in Cambridgeshire, with
OL,16,F29.6C in the classroom by the end of
OL,17,Fthe school day, while schools in West
OL,18,FSussex and Suffolk recorded peaks of
OL,19,F28.3C and 28.2C respectively.
