OL,3,CWarning over 'worryingly hot'
OL,4,Cclassrooms as climate change worsens
OL,5,Cheatwaves
OL,7,FRoger Harding, director of Round Our
OL,8,FWay, which describes itself as a not-
OL,9,Ffor-profit supporting people impacted
OL,10,Fby climate change in the UK, said:
OL,11,F"This data reveals the worryingly hot
OL,12,Ftemperatures our children are starting
OL,13,Fto face in the classroom thanks to
OL,14,Fclimate change.
OL,16,F"Hard-pressed teachers have told us
OL,17,Fabout children this summer who have
OL,18,Ffainted or even vomited due to the
OL,19,Fhigh heat, and there are many more who
OL,20,Fsimply struggle to concentrate.
